      "message": "(L187 does the `function.isBuiltin()` check, so I don\u0027t think there is a bug.)\n\nI think this is really good idea. As a starting point that minimizes the ripple effect, maybe every FunctionCall could just have a `fIntrinsicType` enum in it and function calls which aren\u0027t intrinsics can set it to kNotAnIntrinsic or whatever. I can look at that in a followup CL for sure. It will almost certainly be a net savings of LOC :) Adding a whole IRNode type would probably be a lot bigger change but we could look at that next if it seems like it\u0027ll make things cleaner.",
